cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.GT 

The paper deals with the problem of interference in content delivery networks, which is a common issue in wireless communication and falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also focuses on multimedia content (cs.MM) and proposes a novel approach called content adaptive MAC (CAMAC) to mitigate interference. The paper uses stochastic-geometry models (cs.SI) to quantify the gain of CAMAC in content delivery networks. Finally, the paper discusses the distribution of shot-noise ratio, which is a mathematical problem and falls under the domain of graph theory (cs.GT).
